TWENTY-FOURTH NORTHERN MARIANAS COMMONWEALTH LEGISLATURE
THIRD SPECIAL SESSION, 2025 H. L. B. NO. 24-16
A LOCAL APPROPRIATION BILL FOR AN ACT
FOR THE THIRD SENATORIAL DISTRICT
To re-appropriate Twenty-Six Thousand Dollars ($26,000.00) allotted under Saipan
Local Law 20-26 and re-appropriate Twenty-Five Thousand Dollars ($25,000.00)
allotted under Saipan Local Law 23-10; and for other purposes.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE THIRD SENATORIAL DISTRICT DELEGATION PURSUANT TO
CHAPTER 4, DIVISION 1, TITLE 1 OF THE COMMONWEALTH CODE:
1 SECTION 1. PURPOSE.
2 The purpose of this Act is to re-appropriate Twenty-Six Thousand Dollars ($26,000.00)
3 allotted under Saipan Local Law 20-26, Section 2 (r) (1) and re-appropriate Twenty-Five
4 Thousand Dollars ($25,000.00) allotted under Saipan Local Law 23-10, Section 2 (b) for projects
5 in Precinct II.
6 SECTION 2. RE-APPROPRIATION.
7 Notwithstanding any provisions, statutes, laws or regulations to the contrary, the Saipan
8 and Northern Islands Legislative Delegation hereby re-appropriates the amount of Twenty-Six
9 Thousand Dollars ($26,000.00) allotted under Saipan Local Law 20-26, Section 2 (r) (1) and re-

Saipan Local Law No. 24-03
HOUSE LOCAL BILL No. 24-16
1 appropriate Twenty-Five Thousand Dollars ($25,000.00) allotted under Saipan Local Law 23-10,
2 Section 2 (b) for Precinct II, including but not limited to:
3 1. Twenty-Six Thousand Dollars ($26,000.00) to the Division of Parks and Recreation to
4 purchase a riding mower to maintain Commonwealth parks and recreational facilities
5 in Precinct II.
6 2. Twenty-Five Thousand Dollars ($25,000.00) to the Division of Parks and Recreation
7 for the maintenance and improvements of the Commonwealth parks and recreational
8 facilities in Precinct II.
9 SECTION 3. EXPENDITURE AUTHORITY
10 The expenditure authority for the funds under Section 2 (1) and (2) of this Act shall be the
11 Director of Parks and Recreation in consultation with the Secretary of the Department of Lands
12 and Natural Resources.
13 SECTION 4. REPROGRAMMING.
14 Notwithstanding any laws, provisions or regulations to the contrary, funds appropriated
15 under this Act shall not be reprogrammed for any other purpose.
16 SECTION 5. REPORTING.
17 The expenditure authority shall submit to the Chairperson of the Saipan and Northern
18 Islands Legislative Delegation a detail report showing the expenditure of the funds at the
19 completion of appropriations in Section 2 of this Act.
20 SECTION 6. FUND DISTRIBUTION.
21 Funds appropriated under Section 2 of this Act shall be distributed accordingly to the
22 intended purpose and or entity upon this Act becoming law.
2

